						               													<description>What is it all about?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two fleets fight against each other during the game. Their aim is to destroy the enemy&amp;rsquo;s Command Ship. However this is a hard challenge because the game offers several options to obstruct or threaten the enemy&amp;rsquo;s vessels. Planting sharp mines in the route of the ships is one of them, or you may choose to bluff and plant fake mines that look exactly like real ones...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How does it play?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Every turn the active player rolls a die. The die shows how many actions you have to take in your round: 1, 2 or 3. &amp;#10; - After you roll, you can plant mines on empty fields if you want.&amp;#10; - Now choose a ship and spend your actions. Turn, move or shoot. Every ship type has its unique weapons, and specific role in the battle.&amp;#10; - The first player who hits their opponent's Command Ship is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What this game offers:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- short, simple, easy-to-understand rules,&amp;#10;- quick set up, no more than 5 minutes after the second game,&amp;#10;- relatively short rounds (30-45 minutes), no time to get bored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
